-- 1. [Problem Restatement] Determine the radius of the circle given by \(x^{2}+8x+y^{2}-6y=0\). 2. [Key Idea] Complete the squares in \(x\) and \(y\) to rewrite the equation in standard circle form \((x-a)^{2}+(y-b)^{2}=r^{2}\). 3. [Proof] Start with \[ x^{2}+8x+y^{2}-6y=0. \] a) Complete the square in \(x\): \[ x^{2}+8x = (x^{2}+8x+16)-16 = (x+4)^{2}-16. \] b) Complete the square in \(y\): \[ y^{2}-6y = (y^{2}-6y+9)-9 = (y-3)^{2}-9. \] c) Substitute back: \[ (x+4)^{2}-16 + (y-3)^{2}-9 = 0 \quad\Longrightarrow\quad (x+4)^{2}+ (y-3)^{2} = 25. \] The equation is now in standard form with \(r^{2}=25\), hence \[ r = 5. \] 4. [Conclusion] Rewriting the given equation in standard form reveals a circle of radius 5.
